# Authentication & Authorization

This backend uses JWT-based authentication.
OAuth2 (Google) is used only for login.

---

## Login Methods

### 1. Email / Password Login
- Client sends email + password
- Backend validates credentials
- Backend issues JWT
- JWT is returned in response body

### 2. Google OAuth2 Login
- Client authenticates with Google
- Backend receives Google user info
- User is created if not present
- Backend issues its own JWT
- Google token is not used after login

---

## JWT Usage

- JWT must be sent with every protected API request
- Header format:

-------------Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>


- Backend validates JWT on every request

---

## Public Endpoints (No JWT Required)

- `/login`
- `/oauth2/**`
- Test / health endpoints (if enabled)

---

## Protected Endpoints

- All other APIs
- Require a valid JWT
- Missing or invalid JWT â†’ 401 Unauthorized